Class DescribeDataSourcesRequest

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.amazonaws.AmazonWebServiceRequest
      • com.amazonaws.services.machinelearning.model.DescribeDataSourcesRequest

    ReadLimitInfo, java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

    public class DescribeDataSourcesRequest
extends AmazonWebServiceRequest
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
    Container for the parameters to the DescribeDataSources operation.

    Returns a list of DataSource that match the search criteria in the request.

      • getFilterVariable

        public java.lang.String getFilterVariable()
        Use one of the following variables to filter a list of DataSource:
        • CreatedAt - Sets the search criteria to DataSource creation dates.
        • Status - Sets the search criteria to DataSource statuses.
        • Name - Sets the search criteria to the contents of DataSource Name.
        • DataUri - Sets the search criteria to the URI of data files used to create the DataSource. The URI can identify either a file or an Amazon Simple Storage Service (Amazon S3) bucket or directory.
        • IAMUser - Sets the search criteria to the user account that invoked the DataSource creation.

        Constraints:
        Allowed Values: CreatedAt, LastUpdatedAt, Status, Name, DataLocationS3, IAMUser

        Returns:
        Use one of the following variables to filter a list of DataSource:
